    <!-- About Section -->
    <section id="about">
        <h2>About the Project</h2>
        <p>This project explores the representation of diversity in Hollywood, with a focus on the groundbreaking film <em>Spider-Man: Into the Spider-Verse</em>.</p>
        <p>Key questions:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>How does the film challenge traditional Hollywood norms?</li>
            <li>What historical changes led to more diversity?</li>
            <li>What impact does diversity in movies have on audiences and the industry?</li>
        </ul>
        <img src="spider-verse.jpg" alt="Miles Morales in Spider-Man: Into the Spider-Verse">
    </section>

    <!-- History Section -->
    <section id="history">
        <h2>History of Representation in Hollywood</h2>
        <p>Hollywood's history has been marked by both progress and setbacks in diversity. From early stereotypes to modern breakthroughs, explore the timeline of representation.</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>1950s-1970s:</strong> Limited roles for minorities and women.</li>
            <li><strong>1980s-1990s:</strong> Rise of diverse voices, but still underrepresented.</li>
            <li><strong>2000s-Present:</strong> Increased focus on inclusion and films like <em>Into the Spider-Verse</em>.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- Why It Matters -->
    <section id="importance">
        <h2>Why Inclusive Storytelling Matters</h2>
        <div>
            <h3>Emotional</h3>
            <p>Fans connect deeply with Miles Morales as a relatable and inspiring hero.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
            <h3>Logical</h3>
            <p>Studies show diverse movies perform better at the box office and foster empathy.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
            <h3>Ethical</h3>
            <p>Industry leaders emphasize the importance of representation for equity and innovation.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Stakeholders Section -->
    <section id="stakeholders">
        <h2>Key Stakeholders</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Hollywood Studios:</strong> How diversity affects financial success.</li>
            <li><strong>Filmmakers and Actors:</strong> Opportunities for creatives from underrepresented backgrounds.</li>
            <li><strong>Audiences:</strong> The power of seeing themselves on screen.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

